<subSubSection id="93CDD8C6B6E458D30F30F929B9A79626" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA2E8786B71A3821368275301B39E8C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Re-description male</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C3ACA5572066A3530C23022A01C7ACB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="98DC0AFF7D8727ACC837D398B620EFBC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A1A04FA86459AF26D23EA002C3477DE7" captionStart="Figures 11, 12" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 11, 12. Mesembrius spp., habitus, lateral view 11 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂) 12 M. longipilosus sp. nov. (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures11-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557467" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body length: 10.9-11.1 mm. Wing length: 8.0-8.4 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF3A217FAA264E1311A5FF60A3B1EF7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="8ED948C43DEC29CED629ED38485F4AEA" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED344360E7A065DEDCA1A164F7748C8B" captionStart="Figures 52–57" captionStartId="F25" captionText="Figures 52 - 57. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 52 M. copelandi sp. nov. (♂) 53 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♂) 54 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂) 55 M. longipilosus sp. nov. (♂) 56 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♂) 57 M. minor (Bezzi) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures52-57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557486" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">54</figureCitation>
). Eyes bare; holoptic, length of eye contiguity approx. 1/3 the length of ocellar triangle. Face white with dark medial vitta; white pilose; white pollinose. Vertical triangle with black pile in ventral half and at ocellar triangle; yellow pilose in dorsal half; yellow pollinose. Distance between lateral ocellus and eye margin 1/2 width of ocellus. Frontal triangle and gena white; white pilose; white pollinose. Frontal prominence shiny black; black pilose. Occiput black, but strongly white-grey pollinose; yellow-brown pilose, with a row of almost equally long black pile at dorsal eye margin. Antenna reddish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0CE088120DD08E8795DB0A5F42DD65B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="745C555AA059E10AE37400B5B6B5DBF3" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax.</emphasis>
Scutum dark brown with dorsally a pair of vague yellow vittae; yellow-brown pilose. Scutellum uniformly light yellow-brown; yellow pilose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5FCB89F9E9D204559724D09DBA018D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="9EBC6A1216AB74F5BE2CC2CD65C4AF12" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs.</emphasis>
All legs dark brown, except for pro- and mesotarsi which are yellow-brown. All femora and tibiae with long, loose yellow pile. Proleg (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2DCBFDCA4F604A48B0EA7DA187DBEB7F" captionStart="Figures 155–158" captionStartId="F46" captionText="Figures 155 - 158. Mesembrius, proleg, dorsal view 155 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♂) 156 M. tibialis sp. nov. (♂) 157 M. arcuatus sp. nov. (♂) 158 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂). Abbreviations: bt-basitarsus, fem-femur, tib-tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures155-158" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">158</figureCitation>
): Femur with a loose, yellow apical pile brush interspersed with some long black pile; very short thick pile and longer thin black pile at proximal 1/4 ventrally. Tibia with long, black pile, except dorsally. Basitarsus black pilose dorsally, with tuft of black pile on posterior side, short orange pilose ventrally. Other tarsi black pilose dorsally, short orange pilose ventrally. Mesoleg: Femur long yellow pilose posteriorly and posterodorsally, except at distal end where pile is black; short black pilose anteriorly and anterodorsally; ventrally with longer black pile. Tibia long black and short yellow pilose. Tarsi short black pilose dorsally; short yellow pilose ventrally with a few thick black spines. Metaleg (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="184539E7896C33DAFA047DDB5C34866F" captionStart="Figures 189–192" captionStartId="F54" captionText="Figures 189 - 192. Mesembrius spp., metaleg, posterior view 189 M. tarsatus (Bigot) (♂) 190 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂) 191 M. arcuatus sp. nov. (♂) 192 M. nigriceps Curran (♂). Abbreviations: bt-basitarsus, fem-femur, tib-tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures189-192" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557514" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">190</figureCitation>
): Femur very slender; covered with long, thin yellow pile; shorter black pile on ventral 1/4 and at distal end. Tibia with a deep posterior depression in the proximal half which is extended as a groove on the ventral side, demarcated with short, dense black pile; proximal half dorsoventrally flattened; predominantly black pilose. Tarsi black pilose dorsally; orange pilose ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="07D2BDEB2D5D3B61346767346B4D3F55" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="A672247CD6C8FBDA1ABE95CCCB958664" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7F17D3FE1BFFDB023E55A56AF13B2B83" captionStart="Figures 131–134" captionStartId="F40" captionText="Figures 131 - 134. Mesembrius spp., right wing 131 M. copelandi sp. nov. (♂) 132 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♂) 133 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂) 134 M. longipilosus sp. nov. (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures131-134" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557501" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">133</figureCitation>
). Entire wing uniformly dense microtrichose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D08A547A517899C40D44EE842232A634" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="33969BB9095594FE1A4E96BD3B7D60E4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8AD661B0E2A2A7AC0960D7ECAE1991B9" captionStart="Figures 89–94" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figures 89 - 94. Mesembrius spp., abdomen, dorsal view 89 M. copelandi sp. nov. (♂) 90 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♂) 91 M. ingratus (Loew) (♂) 92 M. longipilosus sp. nov. (♂) 93 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♂) 94 M. minor (Bezzi) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures89-94" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557493" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">91</figureCitation>
). Tergite II with pair of very large, yellow triangular maculae; yellow pilose; black marking hourglass-shaped; posterior black marking equal in size or somewhat narrower than anterior black marking, but more vague because of medial white pollinosity; posterior black marking with black pile that posterolaterally extends into the yellow maculae. Tergite III with yellow fascia of variable size, occupying approx. the entire tergite; yellow pilose; with posterior, triangular black marking; black pilose; white pollinose. Tergite IV black; white pilose and white pollinose on anterior fascia, black and yellow pilose on remainder of tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADB6E0E44D4282743D85738C27F46883" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="A649C7B3D6A6333CC2A8C93B199A7215" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Genitalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B01510D4FE1268BE8847D89332BBC164" captionStart="Figures 205–216" captionStartId="F58" captionText="Figures 205 - 216. Mesembrius spp., male genitalia, lateral view 205 M. arcuatus sp. nov. 206 M. caffer (Loew) (nominal morph) 207 M. caffer (Loew) (spined morph) 208 M. ctenifer Hull syn. nov. 209 M. capensis (Macquart) 210 M. chapini Curran 211 M. copelandi sp. nov. 212 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) 213 M. ingratus (Loew) 214 M. longipilosus sp. nov. 215 M. madagascariensis Keiser 216 M. minor (Bezzi)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures205-216" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557518" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">213</figureCitation>
). Epandrium: Dorsal lobe of surstylus somewhat elongated, broadly rounded, with short, black spines on almost entire surface; dorsally long yellow pilose. Ventral lobe of surstylus straight; bare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
